This suggests a focus on mathematical analysis and modeling.

The third likely sub-category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), which deals with the study of systems composed of multiple interacting agents. The paper's discussion of the impact of the nearest interferer on the SIR distribution suggests a focus on the behavior of individual agents in a network.
